Rush Hour Music has called on Rick
Wilhite to oversee a second Vibes New &
Rare Music compilation.

Vibes gets its title from Wilhite's
now-closed Detroit record shop, which
was once a go-to spot for deep and
soulful dance music. Four years on from
the first edition, Wilhite has returned
with 15 selections by artists from
Detroit, Chicago and New York.

"The compilation itself represents
Vibes and the people that represented
the store," Wilhite told Rush Hour.
"Each cut has the representation of who
the artist is and what he really likes
to put out."

There are plenty of big names'
Moodymann, Jovonn, K-Alexi, Orlando
Voorn, DJ Stingray, Josh Milan of Blaze
and Detroit techno group Los Hermanos
all feature alongside lesser-known
artists like Jon Easly. Wilhite himself
teams up with Norm Talley on "30 Years
Later," chips in with a remix of Sean
Tate's "A Matter Of Honor" and appears
as one half of Rick & Calvin with
Calvin Morgan.
